## 6. Key Domain Patterns

### 6.1 Shader Property ID Caching
**Always** cache shader property IDs as `private static readonly int` fields at the class level:
```csharp
private static readonly int MainTexId = Shader.PropertyToID("_MainTex");
private static readonly int BlurScaleId = Shader.PropertyToID("_BlurScale");

// Usage:
ThisMaterial.SetFloat(BlurScaleId, BlurScale);
ThisMaterial.SetTexture(MainTexId, texture);
```
**NEVER** use string-based shader property access like `material.SetFloat("_BlurScale", value)`.

### 6.2 Asynchronous Operations (Coroutines)
All long-running operations use Unity Coroutines:
```csharp
// Pattern: Public method starts coroutine
public void BatchLoadTextures()
{
    StartCoroutine(BatchProcessTextures());
}

// Pattern: Busy flag for synchronization
[HideInInspector] public bool Busy;

private IEnumerator ProcessDiffuse()
{
    Busy = true;
    // ... GPU processing with Graphics.Blit ...
    yield return new WaitForSeconds(0.1f);
    Busy = false;
}

// Pattern: Wait for completion in caller
while (_saveLoad.Busy) yield return new WaitForSeconds(0.01f);
```

### 6.3 GUI Panel Lifecycle
Each GUI panel follows this lifecycle:
```csharp
// 1. Activation
MainGui.Instance.CloseWindows();         // Close all other panels
XxxGuiObject.SetActive(true);           // Activate the panel GameObject
XxxGuiScript.NewTexture();               // Signal new texture processing
XxxGuiScript.DoStuff();                  // Trigger processing

// 2. Processing (in Update or via Coroutine)
private bool _doStuff;
private bool _newTexture;
private void Update()
{
    if (_newTexture) { InitializeTextures(); _newTexture = false; }
    if (_doStuff) { StartCoroutine(ProcessXxx()); _doStuff = false; }
}

// 3. Closing
public void Close() { gameObject.SetActive(false); }
```

### 6.4 Settings Class Pattern
```csharp
// Plain data class — no MonoBehaviour inheritance
public class XxxSettings
{
    [DefaultValue(1.0f)] public float SomeParam;
    [DefaultValue(false)] public bool SomeFlag;

    public XxxSettings()
    {
        SomeParam = 1.0f;
        SomeFlag = false;
    }
}

// Usage in GUI class:
private XxxSettings _settings = new();
private bool _settingsInitialized;

private void InitializeSettings()
{
    if (_settingsInitialized) return;
    _settings = new XxxSettings();
    _settingsInitialized = true;
}

// Save/Load via ProjectObject:
public void GetValues(ProjectObject projectObject) { projectObject.XxxSettings = _settings; }
public void SetValues(ProjectObject projectObject)
{
    InitializeSettings();
    if (projectObject.XxxSettings != null) _settings = projectObject.XxxSettings;
    _doStuff = true;
}
```

